Summary of the Intern role
 The Investment Banking Internship provides student(s) with a hands-on introduction to the role of an Analyst. You will work alongside our banking professionals, from Analyst to Managing Director level, and will gain exposure to a variety of advisory and financing transactions and sector types. The Intern is expected to work on multiple projects simultaneously, with primary responsibilities in the research and analysis related to transaction generation and execution.
 Specific responsibilities will vary and may include conducting industry research, building financial models to analyze potential transactions, preparing client presentation materials, and working with banking teams to execute transactions.
 The primary role of the Intern includes, but is not limited to:

Conducting industry research and building out industry databases;
Preparing presentation materials such as PowerPoint slides and summaries for pitch books;
Working with banking teams to execute transactions; and
Performing in-depth quantitative financial analyses.

Qualifications
 Seeking a 3rd year undergraduate student. The Intern candidate should possess outstanding academic records and have demonstrated strong leadership ability through involvement in extracurricular endeavors such as student government, athletics, and cultural and entrepreneurial activities.
 The ideal candidate will possess the following:

Strong quantitative / analytical skills;
Exposure to finance and accounting and / or quantitative modeling;
Experience with financial modeling and analysis preferred;
Superior attention to detail;
Disciplined work ethic;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
Ability to effectively manage multiple simultaneous project deadlines;
Proficiency in Excel and PowerPoint;
Ability to work in teams; and
Highly-motivated and energetic.

How to Apply
 Submit your complete application package (resume, cover letter and most recent unofficial transcript), including projected graduation date.
